<h1>California Safe Driver<br/>
Registration and Participation Requirements</h1>
<h2>Technical Requirements</h2>
<ul>Each student must create and maintain <b>one individual account</b>. Any
    attempt to create more than one account <b>will result in system lockout</b>.</ul>
<ul>A <b>computer or tablet is required. Cell phones may not be used</b> to take
    the class. Smartphones are permitted only for the Kahoot! component.</ul>
<ul>A <b>stable and reliable internet connection</b> is required. Students must
    test connectivity in advance.</ul>
<ul><b>Camera, microphone, and speakers</b> must remain operational for the duration of the class.</ul>
<ul>A <b>valid email address and mailing address</b> must be provided.</ul>
<h2>Attendance Requirements</h2>
<ul>Registration opens <b>fourteen (14) days</b> prior to the scheduled class date.</ul>
<ul>Students must <b>check in forty-five (45) minutes prior</b> to the scheduled
    start time with valid photo ID and required workbook.</ul>
<ul><b>Continuous on-camera attendance</b> and participation are required.</ul>
<ul><b>Full course completion</b> is required to receive a Certificate of Completion.</ul>
<ul>Certificates are mailed following completion. Please allow <b>up to fourteen (14) days</b> for delivery.</ul>
<h2>Refunds and Course Cancellations</h2>
<ul><b>No refunds are issued for any reason.</b></ul>
<ul>No refunds for late check-in, internet loss exceeding five (5) minutes,
    off-camera time, incomplete attendance, or rule violations.</ul>
<ul>Courses may be cancelled due to low enrollment, weather, or unforeseen emergencies.</ul>
<ul>If cancelled by California Safe Driver, payments may be <b>applied to a future course date</b>.</ul>